Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

I'm sorry to do this to you, but topic this requires some special handling.

The glance_store is not meant to be exposed to users/operators/other libraries.  So it's not like glance or the python-glanceclient.  It's used by glance, and could (maybe) be used by other services, though possibly not in its present state.

There will most likely be a session about refactoring the glance_store at the summit.  I think we should revisit this issue after the summit.  An alternative to waiting that long would be updating the glance_store docs to include a "statement of intent" about the library so that readers have some context and can set their expectations accordingly.

If you want to push this forward, I'd suggest putting an item on the glance weekly meeting agenda [0] for "statement of intent for glance_store", and we can get the discussion started (and hopefully get some suggested text you could use).


[0] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/glance-team-meeting-agenda
